    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bush and Gore, on the Battleground of Ideas</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mary Lamont letter on Sept 8 editorial urges George W Bush and Al Gore to seek to control prices of prescription drugs to be provided under Medicare</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Economic Scoreboard'' (editorial, Sept. 8):</p>
        <p>Prescription drug coverage for those of us under Medicare would be wonderful! But doesn't anyone realize that the plans of both presidential candidates are like a stamp of approval for the drug companies?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Economic Scoreboard'' (editorial, Sept. 8):</p>
        <p>Prescription drug coverage for those of us under Medicare would be wonderful! But doesn't anyone realize that the plans of both presidential candidates are like a stamp of approval for the drug companies?</p>
        <p>George W. Bush and Al Gore have to guarantee some form of price controls to keep Medicare, and its beneficiaries, secure.</p>
        <p>MARY LAMONT  Hollywood, Fla., Sept. 8, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
